> Are there any extra cases that you'd like me to check?

If it's not too much trouble, yes.
In this reanalysis, I am just scanning over all the possible solutions 
of each constraint equation. In the case of generic MAG, when we want to 
get rid of the extra massless axial vector, I found 20 different cases 
to check. I'm doing it, and each case takes a couple of hours in my code 
(every time I do a full check of both the massless and the massive 
propagation, so i do not miss anything, hopefully).

The constraint is the one you get by taking the determinant (eq.26 of 
the draft) and setting f1 and f2 to zero. So each time there is a "new" 
gauge symmetry..etc etc.

Pairwise in the possible variables, i found these solutions:

solutionList = {{cc10 -> cc11 - cc12 - 2 cc14 - 2 cc15 + cc7 - cc8 + 
cc9,
  cc13 -> (cc14 + cc15)/8}, {cc10 ->
   cc11 - cc12 - 16 cc13 + cc7 - cc8 + cc9,
  cc14 -> 8 cc13 - cc15}, {cc10 ->
   cc11 - cc12 - 16 cc13 + cc7 - cc8 + cc9,
  cc15 -> 8 cc13 - cc14}, {cc11 ->
   cc10 + cc12 + 2 cc14 + 2 cc15 - cc7 + cc8 - cc9,
  cc13 -> (cc14 + cc15)/8}, {cc11 ->
   cc10 + cc12 + 16 cc13 - cc7 + cc8 - cc9,
  cc14 -> 8 cc13 - cc15}, {cc11 ->
   cc10 + cc12 + 16 cc13 - cc7 + cc8 - cc9,
  cc15 -> 8 cc13 - cc14}, {cc12 -> -cc10 + cc11 - 2 cc14 - 2 cc15 +
    cc7 - cc8 + cc9,
  cc13 -> (cc14 + cc15)/
   8}, {cc12 -> -cc10 + cc11 - 16 cc13 + cc7 - cc8 + cc9,
  cc14 -> 8 cc13 - cc15}, {cc12 -> -cc10 + cc11 - 16 cc13 + cc7 -
    cc8 + cc9,
  cc15 -> 8 cc13 - cc14}, {cc13 ->
   1/16 (-cc10 + cc11 - cc12 + cc7 - cc8 + cc9),
  cc14 -> 1/
    2 (-cc10 + cc11 - cc12 - 2 cc15 + cc7 - cc8 + cc9)}, {cc13 ->
   1/16 (-cc10 + cc11 - cc12 + cc7 - cc8 + cc9),
  cc15 -> 1/
    2 (-cc10 + cc11 - cc12 - 2 cc14 + cc7 - cc8 + cc9)}, {cc13 -> (
   cc14 + cc15)/8,
  cc7 -> cc10 - cc11 + cc12 + 2 cc14 + 2 cc15 + cc8 - cc9}, {cc13 -> (
   cc14 + cc15)/8,
  cc8 -> -cc10 + cc11 - cc12 - 2 cc14 - 2 cc15 + cc7 +
    cc9}, {cc13 -> (cc14 + cc15)/8,
  cc9 -> cc10 - cc11 + cc12 + 2 cc14 + 2 cc15 - cc7 + cc8}, {cc14 ->
   8 cc13 - cc15,
  cc7 -> cc10 - cc11 + cc12 + 16 cc13 + cc8 - cc9}, {cc14 ->
   8 cc13 - cc15,
  cc8 -> -cc10 + cc11 - cc12 - 16 cc13 + cc7 + cc9}, {cc14 ->
   8 cc13 - cc15,
  cc9 -> cc10 - cc11 + cc12 + 16 cc13 - cc7 + cc8}, {cc15 ->
   8 cc13 - cc14,
  cc7 -> cc10 - cc11 + cc12 + 16 cc13 + cc8 - cc9}, {cc15 ->
   8 cc13 - cc14,
  cc8 -> -cc10 + cc11 - cc12 - 16 cc13 + cc7 + cc9}, {cc15 ->
   8 cc13 - cc14, cc9 -> cc10 - cc11 + cc12 + 16 cc13 - cc7 + cc8}};

I would expect, as i found in the few cases analyzed, the 
proportionality referred to in the draft, and the impossibility to get 
healthy states. But if this does not happen, we will see it. For each 
case, I've gathered residues and masses.

If it is too much, do not worry. I think i'll need a couple of days to 
finish this scan and we can double check later those cases that might 
surprise us.

Best, C.



